$ SQLite: no boolean data type

SQLite does not have a → development/databases/SQL/data-types/predefined/boolean[boolean data type]. However, it understands the keywords `true` and `false` which evaluate to `1` and `0`, respectively.

gh|about-sqlite|/datatypes/true-false.sql||

sa:
  The → development/databases/SQLite/datatypes[five SQLite data types].
